Sec. 2-1432. Membership.
The Task Force shall consist of the following appointments:
Mayor of Miami-Dade County;
Two Members of the Miami-Dade County Board of County Commissioners;
Assistant County Manager for Public Safety;
Representative from the Miami-Dade County Legislative Delegation;
Director of Miami-Dade Police Department;
Coordinator, Neighborhood Resource Team, Miami-Dade Police Department;
Chief of the City of Miami Police Department;
Chief of Police for Miami-Dade Public Schools;
Superintendent of Miami-Dade Public Schools;
Chief of the Juvenile Division, State Attorney for Miami-Dade County;
Chief of the Juvenile Division, Public Defender's Office of Miami-Dade County;
Juvenile Court Judge, 11th Judicial Circuit;
Deputy Division Director of Operations, Department of Children & Families;
Senior Juvenile Justice Manager, Florida State Department of Juvenile Justice, District XI;
Director Delinquency Prevention Services, Miami-Dade County Department of Human Services;
Director of Miami-Dade Juvenile Assessment Center;
Director of the Children's Services Council;
Director of Metro-Miami Action Plan (MMAP);
The President of the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People (NAACP), Florida State Conference Branch;
Up to eleven (11) members who work for or serve on the board of directors of an organization that works with youth and/or crime prevention recommended by the County Manager and appointed by the Board of County Commissioners;
The appointments listed in(a) through (s) may be served by a designee. If the appointment is served by a designee that person serves in the full capacity of the appointment, with all its duties and responsibilities, and not as a proxy. The appointment of a designee by a Task Force member shall be in writing to the Clerk of the Board.
